title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures">[staton-winskel-2010]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em>rigid morphism</fr:em> of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BN.xml"
addr="jms-00BN"
title="Event structure">event structures</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{E}\xrightarrow {{f}}{E'}]]></fr:tex> is a monotone function on events that preserves finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BO.xml"
addr="jms-00BO"
title="Configurations of an event structure">configurations</fr:link> and is <fr:em>locally injective</fr:em> in the sense that for any finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BO.xml"
addr="jms-00BO"
title="Configurations of an event structure">configuration</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \mathcal {C}_{E}^{\mathit {fin}}]]></fr:tex> and events <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_1,e_2\in  x]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[fe_1 = fe_2]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_1=e_2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>I have not checked whether the appropriate <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-004K.xml"
addr="jms-004K"
title="The structure identity principle">structure identity principle</fr:link> holds for the (pre)category of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BN.xml"
addr="jms-00BN"
title="Event structure">event structures</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BR.xml"
addr="jms-00BR"
title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid morphisms</fr:link>. If it does not hold, this would suggest that a new <fr:em>univalent</fr:em> definition of event structure is needed.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
